deck:
Steve Cook was art director and designer for the British comic 2000 AD from 1988 to 2001.
He regularly designs logo's for DC comics and Vertigo with such titles as The Losers, American Virgin, House of Mystery, Knight & Squire, Batman and Red Tornado. He also created the anniversary cover for VERTIGO X, a special edition celebrating ten years of DC's adult-fiction imprint. 
His collaborators include Grant Morrison and most recently, Brendan McCarthy with whom he worked on Spider-Man, Fever for Marvel comics
name: Steve Cook

deck: Avi Arad is a comic book creator for Marvel.  In the 1990s he became the CEO of the toy company Toy Biz and shortly thereafter Chief Creative Officer for Marvel Comics.
description:
Arad came to America during his college years. He majored in business administration and earned his bachelor in 1972.

deck: Creator of The Urban comic strip: The Boondocks.
description:
Aaron McGruder was born in Chicago, Illinois. He moved to Columbia, Maryland when he was six, because his father got a job with The National Transportation Safety Board. Went to a Jesuit school from grades 7 to 9 and then a public high school. Then he attend the University of Maryland, in which he earned a degree in African American Studies.

In the University he created The Boondocks for his campus newspaper, The Diamondback. His Boondocks series was then collected in many trade paperbacks as well as get its own TV adaptation: The Boondocks.

He currently lives in Los Angeles, California.
name: Aaron McGruder
